1. Temporarily Disable The MariaDB Repository
yum --disablerepo=mariadb install nc

2. Permanently Disable The MariaDB Repository
yum-config-manager --disable mariadb

If your system does not have yum-config-manager installed, use:
sed -i 's/enabled=1/enabled=0/' /etc/yum.repos.d/MariaDB*.repo

3. Clean YUM Cache
yum clean all

4. (If Needed) Edit Subscription Manager Plugin Settings
sudo nano /etc/yum/pluginconf.d/subscription-manager.conf
Set:
enabled=0
Then save the file.

Summary of Commands
You can copy and run these, one by one:

yum clean all
yum-config-manager --disable mariadb
yum --disablerepo=mariadb install nc
Or, if yum-config-manager is not found:

bash
sed -i 's/enabled=1/enabled=0/' /etc/yum.repos.d/MariaDB*.repo
yum clean all
yum install nc
